Ranger Help for: skills
=======================

SUMMARY:
Rangers learn skills by spending slots. Each skill has a fixed slot cost;
learning does not consume ordinary experience or Ranger XP.

HOW SKILLS WORK:
- Skills are organized in a TREE. Learning one skill unlocks others.
- Type 'skilltree' to see the full tree with your progress.
- Type 'learn' to see what you can learn right now.
- Type 'learn cost <skill>' to see exact costs and requirements.
- Type 'learn <skill>' to learn it.

SKILL BRANCHES:
  Survival     Crafting, gathering, camping, herb mixing
  Cartography  Navigation, scouting, terrain knowledge, mining
  Hunting      Tracking, stealth, skinning, snares
  Husbandry    Animal companions, calming, training
  Attack       Melee combat techniques
  Archery      Bow crafting, arrow enhancement, ranged specials

TERRAIN BONUSES:
Many skills work differently based on terrain. Skills used in your
primary terrain cost less SP, have shorter cooldowns, and deal more
damage. Your secondary terrain provides smaller bonuses. Some skills
only work in specific terrains - use 'check <terrain>' to see what
works where.

COOLDOWN CATEGORIES:
Ranger skills recover by category rather than all sharing one timer.
For example, a combat maneuver will delay another combat maneuver,
but it will not stop you from doing fieldwork or crafting. Recovery
skills such as rest and camp tend are broader pauses.

CRAFTING:
Rangers are self-sufficient. Use 'make' to craft items:
  make rope           Twist grasses into rope (grass terrain)
  make torch          Carve a wooden torch (wood terrain)
  make fish trap      Weave a trap for catching camp fish
  make tent           Build a tent from rope + wood
  make tools          Craft tools from rope + rock + wood
  make satchel        Expand your wildcraft forage pouch
  make arrow          Carve arrows from wood
  make bolt           Carve crossbow bolts from wood
  make bow            Carve a shortbow from wood
  make crossbow       Carve a crossbow from wood
  make longbow        Carve a longbow from wood
  make trophy         Mount a trophy from a corpse
  make snare <dir>    Set a snare trap in a direction

Basic crafting flow:
  forage -> make rope -> make tent -> camp
  forage -> make torch (for light)
  forage + mine -> make tools -> mine
  skin corpse + forage -> make satchel
  make arrow/bolt + make bow/crossbow -> archery combat

STARTING OUT:
Your first available skill is 'forage'. Learn it, then learn the
skills it unlocks (make rope, make torch, survey). From there the
tree branches into all six categories.

